sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Notebook Controller<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Service as Notebook Service<br/>ClusterIP 8888/TCP
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant PyPI as PyPI<br/>pypi.org 443/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    %% Flow 1: User Accesses Jupyter Notebook
    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accesses Jupyter Notebook
        User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OAuth)
        Router->>Controller: Forward request<br/>mTLS (if service mesh)
        Controller->>Controller: Validate OAuth token<br/>Check RBAC permissions
        Controller->>Service: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8888<br/>mTLS (if service mesh)
        Service->>Jupyter: Forward to localhost<br/>HTTP/8888<br/>No auth (internal)
        Jupyter-->>Service: JupyterLab HTML/JS
        Service-->>Controller: Response
        Controller-->>Router: Response
        Router-->>User: HTTPS Response<br/>TLS 1.2+
    end

    %% Flow 2: Notebook Installs Python Package
    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,PyPI: Flow 2: Notebook Installs Python Package
        User->>Jupyter: !pip install package<br/>Cell execution
        Jupyter->>PyPI: HTTPS GET /simple/package/<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>No auth
        PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package wheel/tarball<br/>HTTPS
        Jupyter->>Jupyter: Install package<br/>to /opt/app-root/lib/python3.9
        Jupyter-->>User: Installation complete
    end

    %% Flow 3: Notebook Accesses S3 Data
    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Notebook Accesses S3 Data
        User->>Jupyter: Execute boto3 code<br/>s3.get_object()
        Jupyter->>S3: HTTPS GET /bucket/key<br/>Auth: AWS SigV4<br/>TLS 1.2+
        S3-->>Jupyter: Object data<br/>HTTPS
        Jupyter->>Jupyter: Load data into memory<br/>pandas/numpy
        Jupyter-->>User: Display data<br/>in notebook cell
    end

    %% Flow 4: Image Build Process
    rect rgb(255, 240, 245)
        Note over Router,Jupyter: Flow 4: Image Build (BuildConfig)
        participant Build as BuildConfig Pod
        participant GitHub as GitHub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
        participant Registry as Base Image Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
        participant ImageStream as OpenShift ImageStream<br/>Internal Registry

        Build->>GitHub: Clone repository<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
        GitHub-->>Build: Source code
        Build->>Registry: Pull base image<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>Auth: Pull Secret
        Registry-->>Build: UBI9 Python 3.9 image
        Build->>Build: docker build<br/>Layer assembly
        Build->>ImageStream: Push built image<br/>Registry API<br/>Auth: Service Account
        ImageStream-->>Build: Push complete<br/>SHA256 digest
    end
